def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Handle hierarchical columns
    index = data.index

    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) for i in clocs]

    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]
    
    # For multiple levels, unstack each level one by one
    result = data
    for i in range(len(clocs)):
        level = clocs[i]
        result = result.unstack(level, fill_value=fill_value)
    
    # Reconstruct the index
    if rlocs:
        rlevels = [index.levels[i] for i in rlocs]
        rcodes = [index.codes[i] for i in rlocs]
        rnames = [index.names[i] for i in rlocs]
        dummy_index = MultiIndex(levels=rlevels + [result.index], codes=rcodes + [result.index.codes], names=rnames + ["__placeholder__"], verify_integrity=False)
    else:
        dummy_index = Index(result.index, name="__placeholder__")

    # Update new columns
    new_columns = MultiIndex.from_product([data.columns, result.columns], names=[data.columns.name, result.columns.name])

    # Update the result's index and columns
    result.index = dummy_index
    result.columns = new_columns

    return result
